app.get('/users', requireAuth, async (req, res, next) => {
  try {
    const users = await UserService.getAll(); // Fetch from DB
    res.json(users.map(u => ({ id: u.id, name: u.name }))); // Project only safe fields
  } catch (err) {
    next(err); // Delegate to error handler
  }
});
```

---

### 7. 📌 `app.listen` Error Not Handled
If port 3000 is unavailable, the process will crash with an unformatted error. Handle it:

```js
